parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A fuel leak or fuel pump failure can cause a fire hazard, leading to accidents or injuries. It can also cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to loss of control.
symptoms: Strong odor of gasoline
fuel smell inside or outside the vehicle
fuel leak from the top of the fuel tank
fuel pump failure
difficulty starting the engine
loss of gas mileage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Power steering failure can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The steering wheel shakes or pulls to one side
the vehicle is difficult to turn
the power steering fails
the steering wheel feels loose or has play.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Steering linkage failure can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The steering wheel shakes or pulls to one side
the vehicle is difficult to turn
the steering wheel feels loose or has play.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Front axle failure can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The front axle disconnects from the vehicle
the vehicle is difficult to control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission issues can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The transmission slips or slides
the vehicle rides rough
the clutch pedal feels soft or spongy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Low coolant levels can cause engine damage, overheating, and potentially lead to accidents.
symptoms: The "Stop Safely Coolant Level Low" warning appears on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The airbag system malfunction can cause the airbag warning light to illuminate, indicating a potential failure of the airbag system, which can lead to serious injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The airbag warning light illuminates on the dashboard
the turn signal for the right turn stays lit but does not blink.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The key switch failure can cause the vehicle to shut off unexpectedly while driving, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle shuts off unexpectedly while driving
the key switch turns off unexpectedly
the key holder folds in against the column
causing the key to rotate out of the run position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical system failure can cause the vehicle to shut down suddenly, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle shuts down suddenly
the signal light stops working
the whole car shuts down
no electrical or auto operating at all.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Electronic Throttle Module (ETM) can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or enter "limp mode" while driving, which can lead to accidents, especially on highways.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly loses power
surges forward
or enters "limp mode" with a message of "reduced engine performance" followed by "engine service required"
the vehicle stalls while driving
the vehicle has difficulty restarting
the "check engine" light comes on.
